1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 1 MRSA §150-Z is enacted to read:
3 §150-Z. Maine Commercial Fishing Remembrance Day
4 July 21st of each year is designated as Maine Commercial Fishing Remembrance Day,
5 and the Governor shall annually issue a proclamation honoring and recognizing those
6 individuals who have lost their lives fishing for lobsters or scallops, digging clams or
7 actively participating in any other commercial fishery in the State.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill designates July 21st of each year as Maine Commercial Fishing Remembrance
1100 Day and directs the Governor to annually issue a proclamation honoring and recognizing
1111 those individuals who have lost their lives participating in a commercial fishery in the State.
